Hi Spekulatius - Some interesting news today for Senior Housing Properties
Trust (SNH).

HRPT Properties (HRP) agrees to sell 48 buildings to Senior Housing Properties
for $565M

http://biz.yahoo.com/ap/080506/hrpt_properties_property_sale.html?.v=1

==================================

The value proposition take away is that this sale was property that HRP had
owned and managed for the past nine years. A hidden jewel with a huge capital
gain. HRP continues to sell below stated book value and now with this sale,
they will begin to recognize these hidden gains.

From the article:"...
As of December 31, 2007, HRP’s historical investment in these properties was
approximately $397 million, and its depreciated book carrying value of these
properties was approximately $350 million; accordingly, HRP expects to realize
capital gains of approximately $215 million as a result of these sales. HRP has
owned these 48 buildings for an average of nine years.

HRP’s aggregate capitalization rate for these sales based on $40.0 million per
year of current net operating income from the buildings is approximately
7.1%...."

=============================================================
I continue to look for REITs that sell below their stated book value with prime
assets that have good long term leases that generate income. You can get a
pretty good dividend while you wait.

My recent REIT buys include:
